50|$|A <b>trial</b> <b>balance</b> {{is a list}} of all {{the general}} ledger {{accounts}} (both revenue and capital) contained in the ledger of a business. This list will contain the name of each nominal ledger account and the value of that nominal ledger balance. Each nominal ledger account will hold either a debit balance or a credit balance. The debit balance values will be listed in the debit column of the <b>trial</b> <b>balance</b> and the credit value balance will be listed in the credit column. The trading profit and loss statement and balance sheet and other financial reports can then be produced using the ledger accounts listed on the <b>trial</b> <b>balance.</b>|$|R
50|$|An {{error of}} {{omission}} {{is when a}} transaction is completely omitted from the accounting records. As the debits and credits for the transaction would balance, omitting it would still leave the totals balanced. A variation of this error is omitting one of the ledger account totals from the <b>trial</b> <b>balance</b> (but {{in this case the}} <b>trial</b> <b>balance</b> will not balance).|$|R
